Quick comments before we start:
5
- Some Trainers are presumably dummied out, as they do not have names; some of those dummied-out Trainers even include Bulbasaur and Gossifleur, which are not found in Paldea. I have made these Trainers a lighter grey so they are easily skimmed past!
6
- Some Pokmon have explicitly defined genders (denoted with color coding by their name), but some are set to "default." A "default" is most likely not random, and it is obviously not genderless for all of the Pokmon without set genders!
In some previous games, the "default" gender setting prioritized the most common gender for the Pokmon by species, then was set to a value based on the Trainer Class of the person using it (most often matching that Trainer). I can't guarantee that Scarlet and Violet work the same way, but that would be my best guess for any of these!
7
- Some Pokmon have set Abilities, and some Pokmon are set to be random between two of their Abilities - I have clearly labeled which are which!
8
- I'm not sure what it means if a Trainer has the [double] AI tag but isn't actually set to be a double battle, but my best guess is that those are Trainers who can be partnered with other single Trainers in Multi Battles (perhaps including the player?) while the five Trainers more explicitly designated as "double battles" challenge the player alone to a Double Battle.
9
- Although AI flags exist for item use and switching Pokmon, these appear to be set to false for every Trainer on this list - I would love to know if anyone knows whether or not NPC Trainers in this game ever use items or switch Pokmon and what lets them do so!
10
- Lastly... THIS SHEET CONTAINS STORY SPOILERS!! Obviously!!! Please be mindful of that! If it helps to say so, Trainers 437 through 440 appear to be used for the final bosses of the game, so stay away from that area unless you want to see that!!
11
Okay... LET'S GO!
